Slice bitter melon in half lengthwise and remove seeds using a spoon. Thinly slice crosswise and place in a bowl; top with enough salted water to cover. Soak for 5 minutes; drain. Combine dashi kombu, soy sauce, sake, mirin, and sugar in a small bowl until marinade is well mixed. Place beef short ribs in a microwave-safe bowl and pour in marinade; marinate for 30 minutes. Stir bitter melon, onion, konnyaku, ginger, and garlic scape into beef mixture. Cook beef in the microwave for 4 minutes. Mix 2 teaspoons water and cornstarch together in a small bowl until dissolved; stir into beef mixture. Cook beef in microwave for 1 minute more. Spoon rice into bowls and top with beef and myoga.